1.557 26 −19.18 1.193 1.3721 1.676 At 100 ° C ( 373.15 K , 212 ° F ) , saturated sodium chloride brine is about 28 % salt by weight .
At 0 ° C ( 273.15 K , 32 ° F ) , brine can only hold about 26 % salt .
The thermal conductivity of seawater ( 3.5 % dissolved salt by weight ) is 0.6 W / mK at 25 ° C .
The thermal conductivity decreases with increasing salinity and increases with increasing temperature .
The graphs and online calculations in this page plot thermal conductivity for varying salinity and temperature :
The salt content can be determined with a salinometer .
